# module notes

The notes block is the developer's private scratchpad. It is always stripped during compilation — it never appears in the final prompt payload and this template is never executed by the compiler.

`# notes` is the designated home for deferred work, future ideas, and open questions. Because the compiled prompt explicitly forbids the model from emitting `TODO`, `FIXME`, placeholder, or stub code, anything that is not ready to implement yet belongs here — in the spec file, out of the output entirely.

# entity Output

(none — this block is always dropped before the render loop)

# rule

- The compiler drops all notes blocks before iterating for rendering. This template file is never loaded at runtime.
- notes content is never transmitted to an AI model. This is a firm privacy and signal-density guarantee — developer scratchpad stays local, always.
- This file exists for documentation only: to make the drop behavior explicit, discoverable, and part of the same extensible template registry as every other directive.
